<br>
 Ask once if I say no, then please /tell ok sorry to bother and move on.  If you want to try and change my mind do it in one sentence.  Treat it like a petition give me all the info right up front if you don't I'm likely to say no right up front. &quot; /tell Traz I'm at this location, I have druid for port, ill pay you this much, please help&quot;. I ususally get &quot;Can you help me Sir Cleric?&quot;<br>
  I'm going to say NO to that, because I know the next sentence is &quot;I'm in the lord room in lower guk I'm all alone because my group left and I got 3 corpses here but I don't no where they all are.<br>
<br>
   You got to think of it like this, I've been 49 + for about 5-6 months ?  I was also first Cleric on Vazaelle with the Cleric Epic (thanks IV). I was well known as a Cleric early on on Vazaelle and Ive goten 1000's of request for rez. You do not know most of the time what your getting yourself into when you say you'll help. Some rez requests are a 10 sec click of my stick, Some rez requests have turned into a 2 hour CR because there group left them. You get burned a few times on rez request it toughens you to say NO the next time. <br>
<br>
 As for money I think of it like this. I don't require money but your more likely to bribe me if I don't know you. I never ask for money its either offered or not. If you didnt give me any money at the end and I don't know you better kiss my ass with some cleric lovin (/t traz you clerics rock I love you guys!)  or you won't most likely get another. This is debatable if you can in the future provide me with a service.. Druids are (for the most part) are never turned down for rezzes or expected to provide cash or cleric lovin, But of course they will be asked in the future for a port. (theyll be asked politely if I'm turned down I thank them and move on.)<br>
<br>
 This server unfortunatly treats Clerics as vending machines and think just because we can we have to help. We are real people trying to accomplish things in this game just like you. If I'm sitting in EC tunnels at 60 there is a reason I'm there and it not because I'm bored so I'll sit there waiting for a rez request. <br>
   Don't get me wrong I love helping the young newbies that get into trouble and fall down the well in befallen because they didnt know better. But lets face it if your smart enough to do a /who all 60 cleric, your probably passed the newbie stage. <br>
<br>
Just my oppinion<br>
Traz<br>
