You want to piss off a cleric that doesn't go /role or /anon (like myself) ?  Be a druid or a wizard that's anon, and ask me for a res.  I *will* ask you if you are anon to keep people from bugging you for help, and if you say yes, I will not be a happy cleric.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Conversely, if I gave you a free res and you're a wizzie or a Druid, don't even *think* about trying to charge me for a port within 3 minutes of you getting your res.  I've had that happen twice, and I'll never help those people again. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/18/01 11:42:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I dont get mad easy but...</span><hr size=1> Clerics have a right to refuse a res, and a right to charge for a res.  It's a pretty significant mana/time investment, and many clerics are poor as it is from peridots.<br>
<br>
