However, in this case, it's pretty lame for the person in question to ask for plat when you had helped him in the past. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucaylanvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caylan Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 234<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/18/01 11:46:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I dont get mad easy but...</span><hr size=1> Heh I just try to help alot of clerics get clicky sticks so there are better odds they will be close, not busy or in mah groups.  No group rocks more than one with a cleric epic in it <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usiggymk5.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SiggyMk5</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 265<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/18/01 11:56:35 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www-scf.usc.edu/~rabiega/sigs/icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I dont get mad easy but...</span><hr size=1> No matter what, resses are a favor if you're asking someone out of the blue.  Simple as that.  Though it may be lame that you helped someone out and then they want cash for a res, that's the way these things work sometimes.<br>
<br>
When I need a res my search usually goes something like this:<br>
<br>
First I do a who search for all my friends who are res-capable clerics.  If any of them are nearby, I'll ask them, if not, I'll then do a search for druids and wizards I know so that I can arrange for a port if possible for my cleric friend.  After I've contacted my porting friend I'll tell my distant cleric friend what my situation is, and if they can't come they can't come.<br>
<br>
If they can't, I'll start doing a cleric search for zones near my corpse, and I'll start asking, usually it goes something like this:<br>
<br>
/tell cleric_01: Heya, sorry to bother you, but I got myself moronically killed at gimp_location and was wondering if you were free for a res.  I [can/can't] arrange for a port.<br>
<br>
cleric_01 tells you, "Sorry, I'm busy."<br>
<br>
/r "Okay, sorry to bother you, thanks."<br>
<br>
/tell cleric_02 "Heya....."<br>
<br>
Eventually I usually get a cleric to help me.  I always offer cash or gems after a cleric I don't know resses me, the amoung depending on how much trouble they went to and what I had on my corpse when I died.  I also put them on the "will go out of my way to summon corpse for" list.<br>
<br>
Now, being a 51+ SK I get corpse summon requests out of the blue, too, which are totally vicious as they eat a huge chunk of mana (700) for a SK, have a difficult to acquire, expensive component that's a pain to haul around, and usually require a trek to a dangerous dungeon (though thankfully not too far into one).  When I have a coffin on me (which I try to do whenever possible) and am not otherwise occupied, I usually try to help, but there's a much higher chance of me coming to help if sumone tells me they have ports lined up, will reimburse me for the cost of the coffin, or best of all, have a coffin for me to use for them.<br>
<br>
The point of that whole sidetrack being, in my experience, most people (clerics and wizards, though druids are not so reliable given the high d00d population in the class) are kind and like to help when it doesn't require a huge investment of time/money on their part, but it's not often that they aren't in a group, going to a group, or camping a rare spawn or good solo spawn which they might lose if they left.  Thus, any request must be treated with the expectation of failure, not due to rudeness or lack of caring, but because of other engagements.  And though, in m book, asking for money up-front is lame, it is understandable and acceptable. <p><p><center><img src="http://www-scf.usc.edu/~rabiega/sigs/april.jpg"><br><i>Sslanis Soulforge<br>It's not whose habitat it is, it's how hard you hit it</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uscy46.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scy46</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/18/01 12:04:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I dont get mad easy but...</span><hr size=1> *is guilty of doing / all 49 60 cler* I won't ask unless your relatively close by ... and I don't mind dropping some plat for a rez *usually 50-100pp, depending if they only come at the mention of money*<br>
